case.name: Trinh v Minister for Immigration & Citizenship [2008] FCA 299 (7 March 2008)

citation.tocase: Raikua v Minister for Immigration & Multicultural & Indigenous Affairs [2007] FCA 370 , 158 FCR 510
citation.text: 6 In the present Application it is considered that leave to appeal should be refused. The decision of the Federal Magistrate was correct. There is no relevant distinction between either ss 351 or 417 and no distinction between the present case and the decision in Raikua v Minister for Immigration & Multicultural & Indigenous Affairs [2007] FCA 370 , 158 FCR 510. It is considered that the application has no prospects of success for the reasons given in SZJLM v Minister for Immigration & Citizenship [2008] FCA 300.
